title: Tobler's Law
number: 1300
---

One geographic principle to consider is Tobler's first law of geography:

"everything is related to everything else, but near things are more related than distant things"

Discussion:

How do you understand this observation? Apply and explain in your own experience of the world.

![New Yorker cover showing "View of the world from Ninth Avenue," by Saul Steinberg](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/vkcworkshops/introspatialmethods/gh-pages/img/newyorkerviewfromny.png){:height="60%" width="60%"}
